{"author":{"id":"458c2786e2fb21c7f2463be283bdb1d457c6c22ed9854985782318ab918e2e3f"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1459954515,"nonce":"F9umpAybgU3e+1L4aPJ/Qt+EMSQ=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWUxNDYzNDAzNjM=","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/716","origin":"github"},"title":"DESeq2 Wrapper is a bit opaque in how it works","message":"I'd like to understand how the Galaxy wrapper for DESeq2 translates the factors and factor levels into an experimental design and how the contrasts are setup. A quick look for the R code turned up nothing since the script used is embedded somewhere in a dependency. I have a few suggestions:\n1. Add information to the `help` section of the tool that explains how the experimental design is created from various factors (it's particularly unclear how multiple factors are handled).\n2. Add information to the `help` section of the tool that explains how the contrasts are generated (which factors and levels, etc.). Again, this is especially important in multifactorial designs.\n3. Add headers to the output tables that describe the design formula, the contrast, and include a header for each column.","files":null}]}